{"title_page": "List of terrorist incidents in April 2020", "text_new": "{{For|other incidents in 2020, and an outline of what is excluded from or included in this list|List of terrorist incidents in 2020}}\n{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\nThis is a list of some of the [[terrorism|terrorist]], alleged terrorist, or suspected terrorist incidents which took place in April 2020, including incidents by [[violent non-state actor]]s for [[politics|political]], [[religion|religious]], or [[ideology|ideological]] motives.\n\n== Guidelines ==\n*To be included, entries must be [[Notability in the English Wikipedia|notable]] (have a stand-alone article) and described by a consensus of [[WP:Reliable sources|reliable sources]] as \"terrorism\".\n*List entries must comply with the guidelines outlined in the manual of style under [[MOS:TERRORIST]].\n*Casualties figures in this list are the total casualties of the incident including immediate casualties and later casualties (such as people who succumbed to their wounds long after the attacks occurred).\n*Casualties listed are the victims. Perpetrator casualties are listed separately (e.g. ''x (+y)'' indicate that ''x'' victims and ''y'' perpetrators were killed/injured).\n*Casualty totals may be underestimated or unavailable due to a lack of information. A figure with a plus (+) sign indicates that at least that many people have died (e.g. 10+ indicates that at least 10 people have died)&nbsp;\u2013 the actual toll could be considerably higher. A figure with a plus (+) sign may also indicate that over that number of people are victims.\n*If casualty figures are 20 or more, they will be shown in '''bold'''. In addition, figures for casualties more than 50 will also be <u>'''underlined'''</u>.\n*Incidents are limited to one per location per day. If multiple attacks occur in the same place on the same day, they will be merged into a single incident.\n*In addition to the guidelines above, the table also includes the following categories:\n:: {{legend|#E0FFFF|0 people were killed/injured by the incident.}}         <!-- light green      |style=\"background:#E0FFFF;text-align:left\"  -->\n:: {{legend|#B6FCB6|1\u201319 people were killed/injured by the incident.}}     <!-- light green      |style=\"background:#b6fcb6;text-align:left\"  -->\n:: {{legend|#FFFF66|20\u201349 people were killed/injured by the incident.}} <!-- light yellow     |style=\"background:#FFFF66;text-align:left\"  -->\n:: {{legend|#FED8B1|50\u201399 people were killed/injured by the incident.}} <!-- light orange   |style=\"background:#FED8B1;text-align:left\"  -->\n:: {{legend|#FA8072|100+ people were killed/injured by the incident.}}   <!-- light red         |style=\"background:#FA8072;text-align:left\"  -->\n\n== List ==\nTotal incidents: {{table row counter|id=terrorIncidents2020April|ignore=1}}\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" id=\"terrorIncidents2020April\"\n|-\n!Date\n!Type\n!data-sort-type=\"number\" | Dead\n!data-sort-type=\"number\" | Injured\n!Location\n! class=\"unsortable\" |Details\n!Perpetrator\n!Part of<br />\n|-\n|4\n|Stabbing \n|style=\"background:#B6FCB6;text-align:left\"|2\n|style=\"background:#B6FCB6;text-align:left\"|5\n|[[Romans-sur-Is\u00e8re]], France \n|'''[[2020 Romans-sur-Is\u00e8re knife attack]]''': Two people were killed and five others wounded in a mass stabbing in [[Romans-sur-Is\u00e8re]], [[Auvergne-Rh\u00f4ne-Alpes]], [[France]]. The perpetrator is a 30-year-old [[Sudan|Sudanese]] [[Asylum in France|asylum seeker]] and was arrested at the scene. French police have launched a [[terrorism in France|terrorism]] investigation. Two other people related to the attacker were arrested later.<ref>[https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-52165522 Romans-sur-Is\u00e8re: France launches terror probe after knife attack]</ref><ref>[https://www.france24.com/en/20200404-knife-attack-leaves-two-dead-in-french-town-of-romans-sur-is\u00e8re-mayor-says Terrorism probe launched after knife attack in southeast France leaves two dead]</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sudouest.fr/2020/04/05/attaque-de-romans-sur-isere-le-point-sur-l-enquete-7388574-6093.php|title=Attaque de Romans-sur-Is\u00e8re : le point sur l\u2019enqu\u00eate|website=sudouest.fr|language=French|date=5 April 2020}}</ref>\n|Abdallah Ahmed-Osman\n|[[Islamic terrorism in Europe]] \n|-\n|5\n|Suicide bombing\n|style=\"background:#B6FCB6;text-align:left\"|7\n|style=\"background:#E0FFFF;text-align:left\"|0\n|[[Amchide]], [[Cameroon]]\n|Seven people were killed when two suicide bombers blew up in Amchide, Far North Region, Cameroon. [[Boko Haram]] militants from [[Nigeria]] is suspected behind the attack.<ref>https://www.france24.com/en/20200406-suicide-bombers-kill-several-in-northern-cameroon-boko-haram</ref>\n|[[Boko Haram]] (suspected)\n|[[Boko Haram insurgency]]\n|-\n|6\n|Shooting\n|style=\"background:#FFFF66;text-align:left\"|'''20'''\n|style=\"background:#E0FFFF;text-align:left\"|0\n|[[Bamba, Gao Region|Bamba]], Mali\n|In the early morning, Islamic militants attacked a military base in the northern town of Bamba, [[Gao Region]], Mali. Twenty [[Mali Armed Forces|soldiers]] were killed, apparently by an [[Islamist]] group.<ref>https://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2020/04/06/northern-mali-attack-leaves-20-soldiers-dead.html</ref>\n|[[Ansar al-Sharia (Mali)]] (suspected)\n|[[Mali War]]\n|-\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Lists of Terrorist Incidents}}\n{{Portal bar|Lists}}\n\n[[Category:April 2020 crimes|*Terrorism]]\n[[Category:Lists of terrorist incidents in 2020|03]]\n", "text_old": "{{For|other incidents in 2020, and an outline of what is excluded from or included in this list|List of terrorist incidents in 2020}}\n{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\nThis is a list of some of the [[terrorism|terrorist]], alleged terrorist, or suspected terrorist incidents which took place in April 2020, including incidents by [[violent non-state actor]]s for [[politics|political]], [[religion|rel